## 13. Caddy deployment

Caddy was installed directly on Ubuntu rather than as a Docker service.

Configuration:

```caddyfile
wavestack.duckdns.org {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:5173
}

api.wavestack.duckdns.org {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3000
}
```

Configuration path:

```text
/etc/caddy/Caddyfile
```

Service:

```text
caddy.service
```

Caddy was enabled and running under systemd and eventually listened on:

```text
*:80
*:443
```

This means Caddy configuration is currently server-local and is not necessarily represented or restored by the repository deployment workflow.

