## 16. PostgreSQL initialization failure

PostgreSQL’s first initialization stopped partway through because migration `010` attempted to reference:

```text
app_listening_events.created_at
```

The actual column was:

```text
started_at
```

The failure prevented creation of:

```text
app_listening_events_combined
```

Because PostgreSQL Docker initialization scripts run only when the data directory is new, restarting the partially initialized database did not automatically rerun every missing migration. Later migrations were skipped.

The repository’s corrected migration maps:

```sql
started_at AS created_at
```

Manual application of:

```text
infra/postgres/migrations/010_listening_archive_readthrough.sql
```

created the missing combined listening-events view. 

### Required permanent repository fix

The corrected migration must remain committed and be tested against a completely empty PostgreSQL volume. Fresh-database CI should fail if any initialization script stops or if expected relations are absent.

---

## 17. Missing `title_locked` migration

Because initialization stopped during migration `010`, migration `011` was skipped.

The Drive synchronization code requires:

```sql
drive_tracks.title_locked boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT false
```

The sync failed with:

```text
column "title_locked" of relation "drive_tracks" does not exist
```

Manual application of:

```text
infra/postgres/migrations/011_drive_tracks_title_locked.sql
```

returned:

```text
ALTER TABLE
```

The column was then verified as a Boolean with default `false`, and GraphQL was restarted successfully.  

