## 23. Exact root-cause summary

| Symptom                                          | Root cause                                                                                                | Fix                                                                                   | Status                                                         |
| ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Website went offline                             | Azure subscription credit expired; Azure VM stopped; DNS still pointed to Azure                           | Activate Oracle and move DuckDNS to `141.148.156.24`                                  | Fixed                                                          |
| Oracle did not take over                         | Oracle job only built images; no failover monitor, data replication, container startup, or DNS automation | Manually start Oracle and change DNS                                                  | Manual cutover completed; automatic failover never implemented |
| No public website on Oracle                      | Compose had no Caddy service                                                                              | Install Caddy directly on Ubuntu and configure reverse proxies                        | Fixed                                                          |
| PostgreSQL exited                                | Migration `010` referenced nonexistent `created_at` column                                                | Restart Postgres; manually apply corrected migration using `started_at AS created_at` | Fixed manually                                                 |
| GraphQL exited                                   | PostgreSQL hostname/service unavailable after DB failure                                                  | Restart PostgreSQL, then GraphQL                                                      | Fixed                                                          |
| `app_listening_events_combined` missing          | Migration `010` stopped before creating the view                                                          | Apply corrected `010_listening_archive_readthrough.sql`                               | Fixed manually                                                 |
| Drive sync failed on `title_locked`              | Migration `011` was skipped after the earlier initialization failure                                      | Apply `011_drive_tracks_title_locked.sql`                                             | Fixed manually                                                 |
| Listening events violated user FK                | Browser used old Azure JWT/user UUID against fresh Oracle database                                        | Sign out and sign in again                                                            | Fixed                                                          |
| External request said `No route to host`         | Ubuntu iptables final REJECT blocked 80/443                                                               | Insert ACCEPT rules for 443 and 80 before REJECT; persist rules                       | Fixed                                                          |
| Caddy could not obtain certificates              | Public HTTP challenge could not reach port 80                                                             | Correct OCI rule and host firewall, then restart Caddy                                | Fixed                                                          |
| API root returned `404`                          | API is mounted at `/graphql`, not `/`                                                                     | Test `/graphql`                                                                       | Expected behavior                                              |
| Browser library appeared despite empty Oracle DB | Same browser origin retained localStorage/Apollo state                                                    | Export local state and prepare database importer                                      | Export completed; import unconfirmed                           |
| First Drive sync was extremely slow              | Fresh catalog, 4,000+ files, artwork and metadata inspection, one CPU                                     | Run in background and monitor                                                         | Last known running                                             |
| Thumbnail `404`s                                 | Some tracks lacked usable artwork                                                                         | Use fallback artwork and continue                                                     | Nonfatal                                                       |

The full web recovery path and exact firewall/Caddy fixes are documented in the source conversation. 

