## 24. Data that may still be missing

Because Oracle started with fresh volumes, the following Azure-origin state was not confirmed as migrated:

* Original PostgreSQL user records
* Complete listening-event history
* Original event timestamps and play counts
* Favorites not present in the browser export
* Playlists not present in the browser export
* Other users’ account libraries
* Neo4j recommendation graph
* RabbitMQ queues
* Locally uploaded files from `/app/uploads`
* Thumbnail cache
* Any Docker-volume-only metadata
* Any local Azurite data

Google Drive can reconstruct the shared music catalog, and the browser export can partially reconstruct one account, but neither replaces a full Azure PostgreSQL/Neo4j/uploads backup.

The Azure managed disk should therefore be preserved for possible forensic recovery.

